caption: 5 stars is way overrated. Had the pizza and it was very good and top quality but could be matched by many pizza joints across the 5 boroughs. Tiny pizza for $25.
Fantastic service. I appreciate the distance they have the inside dining set up along with the dividers. Food was great. I had the "Ask Mom" cocktail... delicious.
Like the pizza

Pizza and burgers! Like for real though?! For handheld meals this takes the cake. Crunchy crust with fresh ingredients goes such a long way when it comes to pizza and this place hits both of those check marks. The pretzel bun on a burger with cheese draping over the patties is so hard to say no to. All in all I really can't wait to go back here. Unfortunately these pictures were from pre Covid so you most likely will be taking your food to go, but I promise it will be worth the wait of you taking it home or to your car to eat!
(Translated by Google) The burgers here are the best! !! Because it's volumey, it's for people who eat a lot!  (Original) ここのハンバーガーは、最高に美味しい！！ ボリューミーだから、たくさん食べる人向け！
i could serenade the food here!

If this review shows up with one star that is because google whipped the review away from me before I could finish putting in all the stars. THIS IS THE PIZZA THAT IS SERVED IN HEAVEN. Never dined here, ate pizza one time from there and it was pretty great👍🏿

I ordered the MVP through uber eats. It was delicious with really yummy just burnt cheese on the edges if you're into that. So you're probably wondering why I only gave 2 stars for such a good pizza. Well it lacked it's really yummy sauces on one of the edges which shows carelessness in making it. It also was so small! This costs 19 dollars for what I would call a personal pizza. They call it a whole pie, so i ordered it for 2. I mean, fine, some "gourmet" pizza places are like that. They should call it what it is though, a personal pie. On top of that, they charge an extra 3 to 5 dollars for every topping you get. I  ordering banana peppers as an extra topping for 3 dollars. They didn't even bother to bake them on the pizza. Three dollars for a cup of banana peppers on the side? Who does that?
Love Detroit style square pizza. Has a few locations in NYC now. I always recommend this pizza restaurant to anyone who visits!

Loved this spot. Ordered the waffle fries which were nice and crispy. Their spicy chicken sandwich was also very savory and the spice was nice. Lastly we ordered the pepperoni pizza which came out beautifully. Left stuffed and will be back again.

Good square pizza and really nice brioche burgers. Not super quality food b/c a bit greasy, but very good for what it is. Venue is clean and somewhat stylish, but service is a bit cold. They deliver, so that's cool.

Good enough, but outrageous prices even for Williamsburg. I really thought they had missed half of the order when I saw how much food we got for $80.

Also, no one came to check on us/ask if we needed anything. They did however bring the check right away. We  needed napkins and wanted dessert! Will not be returning. Not worth the wait or money.
I don’t like this place

Delicious food with great service and staff even during covid with everything being harder on them im sure. We got the Le big matt with bacon and chopped cheese waffle fries, wings and a big al pizza with the blitz cocktail and everything was delicious. Thanks for facilitating a well needed night out!

I really wanted to like this place as some of the reviews are pretty positive and the pictures look really good.  I am really bummed as the pizza was not good at all.  One pie was burned and the taste is definitely less to be desired.  I will pass on this one.

When my food was finally delivered 45 minutes after the scheduled time via Seamless, it was cold and soggy. This is not because of time in transit, as I was tracking on the app and the driver was waiting there long before the order was finally listed as ready. Inexcusable. If it were my restaurant, I'd be embarrassed to serve this, especially at the price point. Around 80 for a greasy cold pizza, a soggy cold burger with soggy cold fries, and a hard chicken sandwich. Never again.

Wanted to support local businesses during lockdown, so ordered a pizza and a broccoli salad for takeout. $36 before tax/tip. Bit much but sure, should be good. Got home, opened boxes and find...small, ice cold pizza that had been made hours earlier, and a small box of broccoli. Pitiful

This place is the one I always prefer. I go to plenty of restaurants but to this restaurant I  constantly return again and again. The stuff is very receptive and the cooking they serve is so good. I would always prefer to have a good meal here. I highly recommend this place.

Honestly,  I didnt have a chance to eat here... but my biggest turnoff was the male hostess that was at the podium. We was very rude and arrogant. And all I was doing was picking up food for someone else.... so freaking sad,that a place that's probably amazing is soured by one person with a nasty attitude and no common sense.

I love this restaurant! They prepare first-cleass dishes, their menu is decent, The cook in that place is a professional, I love a lot tasting all their dishes. The food is consistently fresh and tasty, the service towards the guests  is agreeable. I visit often this place and I not even once was unhappy.  I highly recommend it.

I had been wanting to visit this place for SO long, and went on a Saturday evening. We were lucky and got seats at the bar. The bartender ignored us for a good 20 minutes before we could get drinks, let alone order food. The food was average (after waiting about 40 minute for it, but the burger was barely warm) and I was so disappointed because I heard this is THE place to get a burger. It was fine, nothing memorable. The Detroit style pizza was tasty, but extra extra greasy-- like dripping down my hands. I happen to be from Michigan and while we like a little fat, this was to the extreme. Took another 20 minutes to beg for the bill and yet another 10 just go get a box and to swipe the card. I don't think I'll be coming back because nothing really made my experience amazing and the place wasn't completely full but soooo slow.
Fantastic pizza. SO HAPPY THEY ACCOMMODATE GLUTEN FREE!! Service was also wonderful. Couldn’t have had a better experience

With a bit less attitude from the bartender/host, I would've bumped this establishment an extra star.  Also, the drinks were 85% ice and 15% what I wanted; for $15+ I would've expected a bit better quality of a drink. The food on the other hand was good, I had the Rhony Pizza, and the $25 Le Matt which was pretty good, but definitely not worth the steep price for a burger comparable to a five guys double patty burger. My suggestion is to perhaps train your employees to be a bit more personable because they are the face to your brand and can be the deciding factor between a customer returning or bypassing, also, maybe the price of the Le Matt and drink quality can be improved.

If I weren’t a big fan of Emily or because I was doing my best friend’s farewell party I might give this place an extra star. First of all service is absolutely good, nothing to be complained about. But there was so much excitement about the food before our visit but the best way I can describe the pizza and the chicken burger was that they were ok. And the food wasn’t cheap. I felt it deserved it at Emily, but unfortunately not Emmy Square.
Nice
Amazing PIZZA!!!!  I was lost, and now I've found my love and passion for pizza again!  Seriously, best pizza I've had in 5-10yrs.

Went to this fantastic spot last night. A gem located in Williamsburg but they have many locations around New York.  We were sat straight away and were greeted well by our server. I came specifically for the special burger and that's what i ordered. I got the loaded Zia waffle fries with it. The burger itself was good but from articles I have read prior I thought It would be better with some labelling it the best burger in NYC and for the 25$ price tag. The meat was medium to well done, which is fine for me and all the components paired well together. The waffle fries were slightly too greasy and the cheese sauce was a bit too stodgy in consistency, but overall tasted pretty good and it was a massive portion.  Overall the food was of a good standard and Id love to go back and try different menu items and definitely the pizza. It looked amazing. Our server was also 10/10 which makes the experience so much better.
By far the best pizza I had in New York

As a Detroit native I can tell you that this pizza is the real deal. Combined with the 1st-class service, this pizzeria is a must. I can't emphasize how much I appreciated the staff and how kind and accommodating they were. I would go back for the service alone but the fact that the pizza is amazing doesn't hurt either lol. PS top notch cheese curds as well.

This is one of my coworkers' favorite pizza spot, so I finally got around to coming. I came on a Saturday night, and it was quite full. When we walked in, nobody greeted us and we stood there for what felt like a really long time, and about five minutes after, two waiters came at once to seat us. That was really strange. We snagged a counter seat in the corner and were given menus. I asked for recommendations and the waitress wasn't super friendly, but she told us her favorite and said it depends on your taste preferences. After a while, she came back to take our order, and I got The Tina with pepperoni instead of sausage. Good thing my friend and I weren't in a rush, because the pizza took forever to come out, at least ten or fifteen minutes, if not twenty. I was disappointed too when it came because it wasn't hot! It was already almost cold by the time it got to me, and that was really sad. The Tina didn't have much flavor at all and was very bland; truthfully, I did not enjoy it because it was cold and flavorless. The crust consistency was good though, light yet chewy. My bill came out to be around $21 post-tax, which is definitely pricey for the amount and quality of food. Service was slow, so don't come here unless you have plenty of time!

The over all taste was something similar to Dominos maybe because of the raw green peppers on top .  Maybe  i was expecting something different . This is Jason. Jason lives in Minnesota. Minnesota is not known for good pizza. I use to live in Minnesota and I can vouch for that notion. The pizza in Minnesota ia subpar at best. However and to be fair, I have not had pizza at every pizza establishment in Minnesota. Minnesota's first pizza parlor was called , "Stan's Pie Shack" founded in 1684 by a guy named Stan. Stan is still alive if you can believe it. He's almost 400 years old now and still flippin those pizza pies like you wouldn't believe. That Stan is quite the Stan. Bye friends!  Update: I'm wearing pants now. Much better.
